Simple coding website using html and css

ChatGPT
Creating a simple coding website using HTML and CSS is a great way to practice your web development skills. Here's a basic example to get you started:

Create the HTML File (index.html):
html
Copy code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Coding Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Coding Website</h1>
    </header>
    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>This is where you can learn more about me and my coding journey.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>My Projects</h2>
            <p>Check out some of the cool projects I've worked on.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2023 Your Name</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
